        Nelson was getting more upset as this case was unwound.  I completely understood.<br/><br/>"Seriously man, were you getting raked over the coals at this meeting?" I asked.<br/><br/>"I had to go over everything again, and explain things and thankfully my management is fairly technical.  They also had a lawyer present just to cover the bases.  He asked me a million questions about my business and what kind of contract I had with my hosting clients.  I realized that this might not stand up in court, so I was pretty nervous." Nelson said as quickly downed the rest of his second coffee."Well, I can't speak for Judge Judy up here, but if you documented everything and maintained some sort of chain of custody of the evidence, you might have a chance in the States." I said.  "But I agree, this is very shaky Nelson."<br/><br/>"I was feeling like total crap, Chief!  After the meeting her fate was pretty much sealed. She was going to be terminated.   Did I mention that she had a B1 visa, so that meant she would probably have to go back to her home country only a few months after her husband had finally moved to Canada!!!"<br/><br/>"Good grief." I lamented.  Now I was getting depressed.<br/><br/>"So a few hours later they called her into the conference room and had a meeting. While she was in there, I had to do my job and disable all of her accounts on the systems and remove her machine from the floor.<br/><br/>I never actually saw her after the meeting, which is probably a good thing. This was probably the most difficult thing that I have ever had to do in my career.  I have worked 120 hour weeks, I have stayed up for three days trying to recover critical data from a file server, and I have dealt with hackers and virii.  Let me tell you Chief, they are nothing compared to having to carry away a friend's machine after she is fired based on information that I provided." Nelson said, clearly drained from our conversation.<br/><br/>Nelson and I spent the rest of the afternoon discussing happier geek topics and putting a hurt on the café's bandwidth bill.<br/><br/>Neither of us transferred any large files.<br/><br/>(Aside)<br/><br/>This was a bit different that my past case files, as it was relayed to me by a friend of mine.  I hope that while reading this case file, the message was loud and clear.<br/><br/>Doing the right thing is almost always the right thing to do - but it's never easy.<br/><br/>What would you have done in Nelson's place?   <br/><br/>(/Aside)
    </div>    
    <div class="spacer marginleftgutter">
            <hr/>
