			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">I agree with Mike.  And happy holidays to everyone.



Chief, as an aside of my own, I live in Ohio and we were pelted with 12 straight hours of an ice storm Wednesday night.  Having lost all power for many hours, I was forced to adapt when it came time for the daily Starbucks run.  I found myself kneeling on the garage floor pulverizing Gold Cost beans in a plastic baggie with a claw hammer.  It looked like the opening scene to 2001: A Space Odyssey.  I kid you not; as I did it I thought "if the Chief could only see me now he'd either admire my dedication to the art or whack me upside the head with a clue banana".  I poured boiling water from a tea kettle over the Gold Coast dust in a coffee filter.  I called it "Caveman Coffee".  Wow, did that stuff pack a punch...

</span>
